"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-08-02-paris-2024-olympics-why-we-lost-to-france-dtigress-boss-wakama\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  D'Tigress head coach, Rena Wakama, has admitted that her players were not at their best in the defeat to France.  The African champions fell to a disappointing 75-54 defeat to the hosts in their second group game in the women's basketball event of the 2024 Olympic Games on Thursday.  Much was expected from D'Tigress after the stunning victory over Australia in their first game on Monday.  The West Africans were, however, totally outplayed by the French in the encounter.  \\\"We did not play our game, we are not ourselves, what helped us secure the win on Monday, we did not bring today,\\\" Wakama was quoted by FIBA.com.  \\\"It's tough when you let another team shoot 63 percent inside the paint.  \\\"It's hard to beat anybody, we need to get back to our ways.\\\"  D'Tigress will face Canada in their last group game on Sunday.  NPFL: Nwoke returns to Sporting Lagos from Enyimba  Transfer: Manchester City confirm deal for Fujino  UK, France, Germany 'under threat' from Iranian missiles - Israel  D'Tigress maintain 8th position in latest FIBA women's rankings  FIBA WWCQ: D'Tigress star Macaulay named in All-Star team  D'Tigress captain Ogoke retires from national team  FG fulfils pledge to D'Tigress for winning 2025 FIBA Women's Afrobasket  War: Not acceptable to attack France - Macron warns Iranian President  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"